INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(4994,'Le Discours d''un Roi','The Kings Speech','allotracker','','','','http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1504320/','','8.4','1080p','en,fr','fr,en','Colin Firth, Helena Bonham Carter, Derek Jacobi','Tom Hooper','','','mkv',4,'','','','','2011-04-19 08:34:29.259712','2011-06-15 16:14:12.407001',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1303172140885.jpeg','image/jpeg',43147,'2011-04-19 08:34:28.579006',2010,NULL,'f',NULL,'f',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,16.5);
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(4995,'Quand Harry rencontre Sally','When Harry Met Sally...','hdfrench','','When Harry Met Sally... is a 1989 American romantic comedy film written by Nora Ephron and directed by Rob Reiner. It stars Billy Crystal as Harry and Meg Ryan as Sally. The story follows the title characters from the time they meet just before sharing a cross-country drive, through twelve years or so of chance encounters in New York City. The film raises the question "Can men and women ever just be friends?" and advances many ideas about love that became household concepts, such as those of the "high-maintenance" girlfriend and the "transitional person".
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(4996,'The roommate','The Roommate','allotracker','','The Roommate is a 2011 thriller film directed by Christian E. Christiansen and starring Minka Kelly, Leighton Meester, Daneel Harris, Matt Lanter, Katerina Graham, Nina Dobrev, and Alyson Michalka. It was theatrically released on February 4, 2011.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(4997,'Into Eternity','Into Eternity','allotracker','','Into Eternity is a feature documentary film directed by Michael Madsen, released in 2010. It follows the digging and pre-implementation of the Onkalo nuclear waste repository on the island of Olkiluoto, Finland. Director Michael Madsen questions Onkalo''s intended eternal existence, addressing an audience in the remote future.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(4998,'Capitalism : A Love Story','Capitalism: A Love Story','','','Capitalism: A Love Story is a 2009 American documentary film directed, written by and starring Michael Moore. The film centers on the financial crisis of 2007–2010 and the recovery stimulus, while putting forward an indictment of the current economic order in the United States and capitalism in general. Topics covered include Wall Street''s "casino mentality", for-profit prisons, Goldman Sachs'' influence in Washington, DC, the poverty-level wages of many workers, the large wave of home foreclosures, corporate-owned life insurance, and the consequences of "runaway greed". The film also features a religious component where Moore examines whether or not capitalism is a sin and if Jesus would be a capitalist.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(4999,'Creation','Creation','allotracker','','Creation is a 2009 British biographical drama film. Produced by Jeremy Thomas, the film was directed by Jon Amiel, and stars Paul Bettany and Jennifer Connelly as Charles and Emma Darwin. John Collee wrote the script based on Randal Keynes''s biography of Darwin titled Annie''s Box.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5000,'Chambre 1408','1408','allotracker','','1408 is a 2007 American psychological horror film based on the Stephen King short story of the same name directed by Swedish director Mikael Håfström, who earlier had directed the horror film Drowning Ghost. The cast includes John Cusack, Samuel L. Jackson, and Mary McCormack. The film was released in the U.S. on June 22, 2007, although July 13 (a Friday the 13th) is mentioned as the release date in the trailer posted on the website.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5001,'Papillon','Papillon','allotracker','','Papillon is a 1973 film based on the best selling novel by French ex-convict Henri Charrière. The film was directed by Franklin J. Schaffner and starred Steve McQueen as Henri Charrière ("Papillon") and Dustin Hoffman as Louis Dega. Due to the exotic locations, the film was considered as very expensive at the time of shooting ($12M), but earned more than double that in its first year of release.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5002,'Elisa','Élisa','allotracker','','Élisa is a French film directed by Jean Becker and starring Gérard Depardieu and Vanessa Paradis. It was released in 1995.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5003,'No strings attached','No Strings Attached','allotracker','','A guy and girl try to keep their relationship strictly physical, but it''s not long before they learn that they want something more. ','','http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1411238/','','6.3','720p','en,fr','en,fr','Natalie Portman, Ashton Kutcher, Cary Elwes, Kevin Kline, Lake Bell, Olivia Thirlby, Mindy Kaling, Greta Gerwig, Talia Balsam, Ophelia Lovibond','Ivan Reitman','United States of America','','mkv',4,'','','','','2011-04-26 08:56:42.220716','2011-06-15 16:14:12.449214',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'nsabrdfront.jpeg','image/jpeg',54750,'2011-04-26 08:56:51.795984',2011,NULL,'f',NULL,'f',NULL,'/m/0cp7w2r',NULL,NULL,13);
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5004,'Dans la brume électrique','In the Electric Mist','allotracker','','In the Electric Mist is a 2009 Franco-American drama/fantasy film based on the novel In the Electric Mist with Confederate Dead by James Lee Burke. It is directed by Bertrand Tavernier, written by Jerzy Kromolowski and Mary Olson-Kromolowski, and stars Tommy Lee Jones in the lead role of Louisiana police detective Dave Robicheaux.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5005,'Le sucre','','gks','','','','http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0078338/','','5.6','720p','fr','','','','','','mkv',4,'','','','','2011-04-26 11:45:14.135589','2011-05-26 07:04:37.592174',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cache.jpeg','image/jpeg',48299,'2011-04-26 11:45:13.736952',1978,NULL,'f',NULL,'f',NULL,'/m/0b87xw8','','',NULL);
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5006,'La couleur pourpre','The Color Purple','hdfrench','','The Color Purple is a 1985 American period drama film directed by Steven Spielberg, based on the Pulitzer Prize-winning novel of the same name by Alice Walker. It was Spielberg''s eighth film as a director (not including the 1971 television film Duel), and was a change from the summer blockbusters for which he had become famous. Filmed in Anson and Union counties in North Carolina, the film tells the story of a young African American girl named Celie and shows the problems African American women faced during the early 1900s, including poverty, racism, and sexism. Celie is transformed as she finds her self-worth through the help of two strong female companions.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5007,'Brest Fortress','The Brest Fortress ','allotracker','','The Brest Fortress is a 2010 war film directed by Aleksandr Kott and written by Ekaterina Tirdatova, Vladimir Eremin, Konstantin Vorobyov and Aleksey Dudarev.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5008,'Animal Kingdom','Animal Kingdom','hdfrench','','Animal Kingdom is a 2010 Australian drama written and directed by David Michôd, and stars Ben Mendelsohn, Joel Edgerton, Guy Pearce, Luke Ford, Sullivan Stapleton, Jacki Weaver and James Frecheville. The film has received several awards and nominations with Weaver receiving multiple awards for her performance, including an Academy Award nomination for Best Supporting Actress .
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5009,'Princess bride','The Princess Bride','hdfrench','','The Princess Bride is a 1987 American film based on the 1973 novel of the same name by William Goldman, combining comedy, adventure, romance, and fantasy. The film was directed by Rob Reiner from a screenplay by Goldman. The story is presented in the film as a book being read by a grandfather (Peter Falk) to his sick grandson (Fred Savage), thus effectively preserving the novel''s narrative style. This film is number 50 on Bravo''s "100 Funniest Movies," number 88 on The American Film Institute''s (AFI) "AFI''s 100 Years... 100 Passions" listing the 100 greatest film love stories of all time, and 46 in 50 Greatest Comedy Films.
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5010,'Et au milieu coule une rivière','A River Runs Through It','hdfrench','','A River Runs Through It is an Academy Award winning 1992 American film directed by Robert Redford and starring Brad Pitt, Craig Sheffer, Tom Skerritt, Brenda Blethyn, and Emily Lloyd. It is a period drama based on the semi-autobiographical novella A River Runs Through It (1976) written by Norman Maclean (1902–90).
INSERT INTO "movies" VALUES(5011,'Pink Floyd: Live at Pompeii','Pink Floyd: Live at Pompeii','allotracker','','Pink Floyd: Live at Pompeii is a 1972 film featuring Pink Floyd performing six songs in the ancient Roman amphitheatre in Pompeii, Italy. It was directed by Adrian Maben and recorded in the month of October using studio-quality 24-track recorders without a live audience.
